==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in the 1690's. From {{etyl|ML.|en}} {{term|abyssalis|lang=la}},<ref name=SOED>{{R:SOED5|page=11}}</ref><ref name=RHD>{{R:RHCD|page=7}}</ref> from {{term|abyssus||abyss|lang=la}} + {{term|-alis||-al|lang=la}}<ref name=WI3>{{R:MW3 1976|page=9}}</ref>. Equivalent to {{suffix|abyss|al}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/əˈbɪs.l̩/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/əˈbɪs.l̩/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪsəl}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# {{context|archaic|lang=en}} Belonging to, or resembling, an [[abyss]]; [[unfathomable]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|geography|lang=en}} Of or belonging to the [[ocean]] depths, especially below 2000 metres (6500 ft): ''[[abyssal zone]]''. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|geology|lang=en}} Pertaining to or occurring at excessive depths in the earth's [[crust]]; [[plutonic]]. {{defdate|First attested in the late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

